# No Environment Branching In Business Logic

- Do not change business/domain behavior based on environment flags (`DEV`, `PROD`, `TEST`, `import.meta.env`, etc.).
- Keep the same resolution and decision logic across environments.
- Environment differences are allowed only for operational concerns (logging level, diagnostics visibility, local tooling).
- If a behavior change is requested for one environment only, stop and ask for explicit confirmation before implementation.

## Examples

- Bad: Different i18n resolution order in DEV vs PROD.
- Good: Same i18n resolution order everywhere; only debug logging differs.
